CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 28, 1957, pg. 2 reads: "Gutted School - Firemen "water down" Elementary School One before a wrecking crew knocked down the masonry walls which were weakened by the disastrous Rankin fire. Besides school books, a $30,000 new medical and dental laboratory in the school was destroyed. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Fire fighters operating hose before burning Elementary School One with barbed wire in foreground, Rankin
